This is the procedure I'm following to create a copy of the template worksheet:

```javascript
let extraRows: number;
let sheetToClone = workbook.getWorksheet('TEMPLATE')!;
let isFirstRow: boolean;
criticalRiskActivities.forEach((criticalRiskActivity, index) => {
  const forms = JSON.parse(criticalRiskActivity.forms);
  forms.forEach((form: any) => {
    const copySheet = workbook.addWorksheet(`Sheet${index + 1}`);
    copySheet.model = {
      ...sheetToClone.model,
      name: `${index + 1} - ${form.abbreviation}`,
    };
}});
```

## The expected behaviour:

I anticipate duplicating the rows and merging them seamlessly to finalize the template, ensuring there are no styling discrepancies, such as this:

